    "summary": "\nEDUCATION:\n1962\t\t\t\tGraduated from college (HBS), Venray.\n1968\t\t\t\tB. Sc. in Physics, University of Utrecht.\n1972\t\t\t\tCertificate of Educational Science, U of U.\n1972\t\t\t\tM.Sc. in Physics (drs.), U of U.\n\nKEY QUALIFICATIONS IN JOB AT CITO:\n\nWithin CITO Mr. Hendricx was working as a senior educational assessment expert. He was responsible for the construction and analysis of the National Physics examination for pre-university education and for some other National Examinations.\nAs a consultant of international projects in Hungary, Romania and Aruba, he trained groups of Hungarian, Romanian and Aruban teachers and professionals in item- and test construction etc.\nHe was involved some years in The PISA-project as a senior Science adviser.\n\nADDITIONAL INTERNATIONAL EXPERIENCE:\n\n1996-2001\t\tConsultant for the BIEHONG project in Hungary. Training a group of Hungarian teachers and professionals in item- and test construction etc.\n1999-2001\t\tConsultant for the AERo project in Romania. Giving all kinds of assistance to the Education Reform Project. \n1999-2006\t\tConsultant in Aruba. Training a group of teachers and professionals in setting up a final examination system and examination program.  \n2004-2006\t\tSenior Science Adviser in the PISA-project.\n2006\t\tMay 1rst., mr. Hendricx retired from Cito (FPU)\n\nEXPERIENCE as a teacher:\n1972-1978\t\tPhysics and Mathematics teacher at a secondary school (Gregorius College in Utrecht) and a Teacher Training College (SOL).\n1972-1995\t\tPhysics teacher at the pre-university faculty of the University of Utrecht. \n2008- 2009\tPhysics teacher at NSG Groenewoud.\n2009-2011\t\tPhysics teacher at Dominicus College.\n2010-2012\t\tCo-worker at Noordhoff Publishers in a team of authors.\n2015-2016\t        Physics teacher at Arentheem College Thomas a Kempis.\n\n\n",
